# MCP Server — Cursor Rules

This is an MCP-native server built with Next.js + TypeScript. When editing code, follow these patterns:

## Architecture
- `src/mcp/server.ts` — MCP stdio server entry point. Add new tools here first.
- `src/lib/agent/` — AI agent logic (streaming, analysis, scoring)
- `src/lib/integrations/` — CRM and data source clients (Salesforce, HubSpot, Gong, etc.)
- `src/lib/demo/` — Rich mock data for zero-config demo mode
- `src/app/api/` — REST + SSE endpoints that wrap MCP tools

## Adding a New Tool
1. Add tool schema to `TOOLS` array in `src/mcp/server.ts`
2. Add handler branch in `handleToolCall()`
3. Delegate to the real module in `src/lib/` (don't put business logic in the server)
4. Return JSON-serialized result with `isError: false`
5. Add test in `src/lib/__tests__/` or `src/mcp/__tests__/`

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Zod for all runtime validation
- Jest for testing
- Tailwind for UI
- Framer Motion for animations

## Demo Mode
All tools should work without API keys. Use `src/lib/demo/` data when env vars are empty.

## MCP Transport
- Stdio: `npx ts-node src/mcp/server.ts`
- SSE: `npm run dev` then hit `/api/mcp/sse` (add this endpoint if missing)
